### Intro:

The intention of this tool is to automate and standardize the way in which the Project Management team reports their statuses both internally and externally. The automation will pull from tools already being used by Cognite.   
The dashboard will include the following: 

1. Project Health   
2. Remaining Budget  
3. Timeline with Jira tickets (and the ability to add if needed)   
4. Sprint Goals   
5. Action Register   
6. Risk Matrix 

For the POC we will be using: 

* Precursive:  \[Hanwha Ocean\] Base Implementation Services ([https://cognite.lightning.force.com/lightning/r/preempt\_\_PrecursiveProject\_\_c/a2XSZ000000p3a92AA/view](https://cognite.lightning.force.com/lightning/r/preempt__PrecursiveProject__c/a2XSZ000000p3a92AA/view))  
* Jira: (We are going to use QuickStart\_Hackathon\_Template: [https://cognitedata.atlassian.net/jira/software/projects/QHT/boards/4312/backlog?atlOrigin=eyJpIjoiMjQ2ZjVkNDBjMDI5NDRkNGIyZGE1ZThiZWM5NGY1ZWUiLCJwIjoiaiJ9](https://cognitedata.atlassian.net/jira/software/projects/QHT/boards/4312/backlog?atlOrigin=eyJpIjoiMjQ2ZjVkNDBjMDI5NDRkNGIyZGE1ZThiZWM5NGY1ZWUiLCJwIjoiaiJ9)) 

### Sign In 

The application's entry point is a login screen, which determines the user's role.

* UI: A clean login page offering two methods:  
  * A prominent "Login with Google" button (for SSO).  
  * A simple form for Email & Password login.  
* Role Logic:  
  * Cogniter: Any user authenticating with an @cognite.com email address (whether via Google SSO or manual login) is assigned the Cogniter role.  
  * Client: Any user authenticating with any other email address is assigned the Client role.

User Data Model:  
User:  
id (unique identifier)  
email (string, unique)  
name (string)  
role (enum: 'Cogniter' or 'Client')  
authProvider (enum: 'Google' or 'Email')

### Defining a project 

They should be automatically created When Precursive Project is switched over to Delivery (similar to the slack channels and google folders). Short term would like a manual way to create.  

* Input Fields:  
  * Project Name: (Required, Text) The client-facing name of the project.   
    * Could pull from Precursive Automatically, and be editable   
  * Precursive (Salesforce) URL: (Required, URL) The unique URL for the project. The system must enforce a one-report-per-URL constraint.  
    * Will be automatically as it is the trigger. If not pulling then text input  
  * Jira Project URL: (Required, URL) The link to the main Jira board for this project.  
  * Client Logo: (Required, File Upload) An image upload field.  
  * Project Type: (Required, Dropdown) Options: "T\&M Billable" or "Fixed Price". This determines if financials are shown.  
    * Drop down, and populated if we don’t have the info from Precursive. Should be able to pull this from Precursive.  
    * Options from Precursive:   
      * Fixed Price   
      * T\&M   
      * SaaS Revenue  
  * Reporting Cycle: (Dropdown) Options: "Weekly" or "Bi-weekly". This provides context for the "Last/Next Cycle" fields.  
* When the user hits create we need to make sure they are authorized to access those projects   
  * Jira: Owner or Administrator  
    ![][image2]  
    ![][image3]  
  * Precursive: Owner or Project Manager  
    ![][image4]

Question: If we don’t do precursive to automatically create the project, when the user populates the URL can we run a job to populate what it can after?   
**\*Key to make sure that the API keys are very protected so that other client info is not exposed.**

### Timeline

I would like the ability to automatically create timelines that adjust everything dynamically if a date of a parent is changed. 

* Currently will connect to Jira to get the start and end date of:   
  * Epics   
  * Stories   
  * Tasks  
  * Subtasks   
* In addition we will need the parent child relationships   
  * Stories and tasks will sit under epics and subtasks under stories and tasks   
* Option to have the percent complete within the bars of the timeline   
* Milestone view or sprint view  
* Links to jira (We are going to use QuickStart\_Hackathon\_Template: https://cognitedata.atlassian.net/jira/software/projects/QHT/boards/4312/backlog?atlOrigin=eyJpIjoiMjQ2ZjVkNDBjMDI5NDRkNGIyZGE1ZThiZWM5NGY1ZWUiLCJwIjoiaiJ9)

### Financials

Need to be shown to manage the clients expectations, as well as internally. This is one area where I think there may be some differences that depend on which type of project you have (defined during project creation/take from Precursive) 

* Fixed Price \- Critical for internal boards to make sure we aren’t going over the budget/not profiting  
* T\&M \- Critical for internal & External views. 

![][image12]

* The Remaining Budget will be pulled when the status is public. If we have the project updating live then pull budget once a day.

### Action Register 

Interactive with client, where we can make comments and add things as complete. 

* Can pull from tasks labeled with a certain label in Jira  
  * Title, the status, Assignee, Due Date, Priority.     
* Can make comments (need to be stored with that action)  
  * Need to keep track of the comments, when they are made, and who made them  
* Client or internal can change the status and make comments  
  * To Do, In Progress, Complete   
* Past due will be red 

![][image13]  
Action ID, Jira ID column  
Ability to turn them on and off

### Risk Matrix

* Need the ability to add a risk or issue directly from the UI  
* Pull Risks from Precursive
